    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-24T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-24T12:00:00-05:00" n="514"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/4–2454: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation at the North
                            Atlantic Council</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d514fn1">Repeated to Brussels, The Hague, Luxembourg, and
                        Bonn.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-24T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 24, 1954—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 11. Limit distribution. Secretary met
                    with <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> this morning<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d514fn2">A copy of the memorandum of this conversation is in file
                        740.5/4–2454.</note> and was informed three <gloss target="#t_Benelux1"
                        >Benelux</gloss> Foreign Ministers had agreed <pb facs="0994" n="950"
                        xml:id="pg_950"/> present to <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> interim
                    committee next week formula to meet <persName corresp="#p_MOLLETG1"
                        >Mollet</persName>’s demands for democratic control <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                        >EDC</gloss>. <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> will see
                        <persName corresp="#p_MOLLETG1">Mollet</persName> this afternoon to attempt
                    satisfy him, and will also see <persName corresp="#p_HALLSTEINW1"
                        >Hallstein</persName> today to endeavor obtain consent German Government.
                    His contacts with French Government officials lead him believe such <gloss
                        target="#t_Benelux1">Benelux</gloss> initiative can be effective. He feels
                    sure Italians will interpose no objection. He hopes <gloss target="#t_IC1"
                        >IC</gloss> can agree April 28 on measures which will permit <persName
                        corresp="#p_MOLLETG1">Mollet</persName> proceed convocation Socialist
                    Congress.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> feels majority for <gloss
                        target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> exists French National Assembly if government
                    pressed issue. He did not indicate great concern over coming to power <persName
                        corresp="#p_MENDESFRANCEP1">Mendes-France</persName> as such but feels
                    circumstances attendant any such change of government in France would cause long
                    and perhaps fatal delays <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>. He feels serious
                    political errors of <persName corresp="#p_DEGAULLEC1">De Gaulle</persName> have
                    eliminated possibility his return to power which otherwise would have been
                    virtual certainty, especially if disaster in Indochina.</p>
                <p>In response Secretary’s outline gravity in US failure bring <gloss
                        target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> into being promptly, <persName
                        corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> said French parliamentarians simply
                    did not believe US would basically alter its European policy though smaller
                    states vividly aware danger caused by failure French leadership. Finally,
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> said possibly Germans
                    should make statement re Saar indicating their ultimate position (which would
                    be, however, contingent on <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> ratification).
                    However, in view atmosphere France especially due Indochina problem, <persName
                        corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> thought it undesirable threaten
                    French with restoration German sovereignty in event <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                        >EDC</gloss> fails.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> promised all possible help and
                        <persName corresp="#p_DESTAERCKEA1">De Staercke</persName> will remain in
                    close contact US officials Paris.</p>
            </div>
